<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ensnare" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ensnare,</orth> to lay snares or nets for: <bibl n="shak. luc 584" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 584</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.243" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 243</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.170" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 170</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.302" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 302</bibl>. <cit><quote>thy beauty hath --d thee to this night,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 485" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 485</bibl></cit>, i. e. has entrapped thee to the advantage of this night.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>